    "notes": "LP is pressed on 180 gram vinyl. Includes a replica of the full color poster of the band, by Norman Seeff, from the original album.\n\n[Back cover]\n℗ & © 1976 Elektra/Asylum Records for the U.S. and WEA International Inc. for the world outside of the U.S.  All Rights Reserved.\nMarketed by Warner Strategic Marketing, a Warner Music Group Company. Made in the Netherlands. LC02982 \n\n[Record labels]\n℗ © 1976 Elektra/Asylum Records for the U.S. and WEA International Inc. for the world outside of the U.S. ... Marketed by Warner Strategic Marketing, a Warner Music Group Company. Made in EU. LC02982 \n\n[Cat #s]\nRRM1-1084 - on spine, on inner sleeve top left, record labels\n8122796161 - on bottom of post production barcode sticker \n\n[Differentiation and identification]\nMost obvious differences from [r6623165] are (i) the \"Made in the Netherlands\" at the bottom of the rear cover of this release vs. \"Made in the EU\" on the other, and (ii) the matrix information is different, indicating a different pressing, cut by Chris Bellman rather than Bernie Grundman.\nTracks A3 and B2 Joe Walsh's Guitar credits are misspelt as \"Guiter\" on the inner sleeve song credits.\n\nRunouts are partially etched/stamped.",
